BEGIN:VEVENT
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Website-cover-images-new-2026-03-19T091423.084.png
CATEGORIES:Talks,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260319T035456Z
DESCRIPTION:Image credits: Arati Kumar-Rao\nJoin us for a conversation by Jeet Thayil moderated by Joshua Muyiwa and Samyuktha Varma. Singing in the Dark: Art Against Genocide brings forth conversations that make us think\, make us question and make us human. We ponder\, or rather assert\, the role of art\, as resistance\, as hope\, as resilience during times of crisis. Thayil’s and Muyiwa’s poetry enriches the conversation as Varma adds depth to our thoughts.\n\n&nbsp\;\n\nThis is in collaboration with Ananya Drishya. 
DTEND:20260324T133000Z
DTSTART:20260324T123000Z
SUMMARY:Singing in the Dark
UID:1217@map-india.org
URL:https://map-india.org/map-events/singing-in-the-dark/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Website-cover-images-new-2026-03-11T100705.390.png
CATEGORIES:Workshops,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260311T101622Z
DESCRIPTION:Image Credits: Poornima Jain-Haveli Textile Collection\nTextile Conversations is designed as a two-part engagement programme exploring material knowledge in the Haveli Collection through dialogue and hands-on practice.\n\nThrough knowledge exchange between collaborators\, each session positions textile researchers and practitioners as contributing distinct forms of expertise - technical\, functional\, embodied and aesthetic.\n\nThe programme draws strongly from the Haveli Collection at MAP\, that consists of over 2741 textile objects and over 2050 archival materials\, all belonging to the Haveli fashion brand established in the 1980s by Poornima Jain in Maharani Bagh\, Delhi. \n\n
DTEND:20260322T110000Z
DTSTART:20260321T060000Z
SUMMARY:Textile Conversations
UID:1214@map-india.org
URL:https://map-india.org/map-events/textile-conversations/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Website-cover-images-new-2026-03-06T095723.726.png
CATEGORIES:Workshops,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260316T070616Z
DESCRIPTION:Image Credits: Sanchita Jain\nJoin us for a lively conversation about cats\, their histories\, myths\, and personalities. Exploring two books on Indian cats\, B. N. Goswamy's The Indian Cat and Olliewanders\, you can swap stories\, challenge common misconceptions\, and celebrate the surprising complexity of our feline companions.\n\nExpect good conversation\, plenty of colour\, and a "mosaic of many cats" who may look suspiciously like their humans\, especially for anyone who suspects they might\, spiritually\, be a cat.\n\nThis event is part of the closing weekend celebrations for The Many Lives of the Cat.
DTEND:20260328T103000Z
DTSTART:20260328T090000Z
SUMMARY:In the Company of Cats
UID:1211@map-india.org
URL:https://map-india.org/map-events/miniature-to-mischief/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Website-cover-images-new-2026-03-19T101011.023.png
CATEGORIES:Workshops,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260319T051406Z
DESCRIPTION:This workshop invites participants to explore touch\, imagination and feminist storytelling through making. Surrounded by Eisma’s playful and tactile world\, participants will create their own hand puppets using socks\, fabric\, and simple craft materials.\n\nWe invite you to bring your stories on themes of care\, transformation\, and the power of gentle voices. Which have been important creatures\, human or not\, that have held you when you have needed it? \n\nDrawing from feminist perspectives that value vulnerability\, creativity\, and shared experience\, we encourage you to give shape and colour to these stories and characters\, and let the sock become puppet characters\, messengers of small\, personal\, and collective stories that are there to speak and listen\, resist or comfort us.\n\nThis event is held in conjunction with our exhibition\, mild tooth of milk\, currently on display at the Dutch Warehouse in Fort Kochi.
DTEND:20260328T093000Z
DTSTART:20260328T053000Z
SUMMARY:the power of puppet companions
UID:1219@map-india.org
URL:https://map-india.org/map-events/the-power-of-puppet-companions/
END:VEVENT
